caption: Great food & drinks

La Josie marries the atmospheres of intimacy and bar together, paired with a drink menu and food that will delight any group. Our server was attentive and knowledgeable of the menu and gave great recommendations. Options for chicken, seafood, beef, and vegetarian will keep everyone happy. We particularly enjoyed the guac sampler, habenero salsa, and several rounds of drinks. Try the el guapo if you like a little spice in your drink. The pollo enchiladas came recommended and for a reason! We will certainly be back to sample more of the food!!
Delicious! Pricey but yummy!
My experience felt rushed, over priced food that is average and the group i left with wanted to eat again after leaving
The vegetarian prix fix menu was basically just salad that wasn't made well at all.

I really hate to write this post since I worked in the restaurant industry but I have to. My boyfriend and I dined here on a Friday and had 5:30 reservations. We came in and was sat on time. The problem was that the hosted decided to sit us at a corner back dark table when there was clearly a table closer to the front near exposed windows.This week in particular Chicago was extremely gloomy and that Friday was a cold but sunny day. Who wants to sit at a dark back table when there was clearly a table near the front next to exposed windows? The good thing is that when I asked to be moved they moved us right away to the table. It left a weird taste in my mouth as to why they would even sit us there in the first place. Oh and not to mention my boyfriend and I are African  American. I really hope that that had nothing to do with it and that the hosted made an honest mistake.

Rated 2 stars due to the poor service I received from the server. Unfortunately, I don’t remember her name but she wasn’t friendly. I felt rushed and 25 minutes after she took our order she returned to our table to say, her shift was ending and a guy named Victor would takeover as our server. That was the most she had said to us while being our server.  Also, the food was not so great. I thought the restaurant had a nice set up inside. However, I wouldn’t recommend to anyone I know.. the poor service was an instant turn off, and I won’t be returning.
Excellent Mexican Seafood.... Must try the Mariscada!!!!
Got the carnitas, al pastor and baja tacos and they were all spectacular. Highly recommend.
Shout out to Chef Chavez!
Great staff and food. First time trying ceviche and it was awesome.
Great food and service
Was really lackluster and beverages selection was very limited. Felt rushed although the place was not crowded.

Food was amazing, very authentic Mexican food along with the drinks. Customer service was great and accommodating, our server Alyssa was excellent and very attentive. Definitely recommend checking La Josie out!!!
A real Mexican authentic food right in the heart of West Loop! Amazing Mezcal program and delicious cocktails!!! my new favorite spot!

Came here a few months ago for outdoor dining and loved it- the food, drinks, service, really everything! For drinks, La Luchador was sweet but refreshing. As for food, we got the salsa trio and the salsa verde was the best I've ever had! Also loved the three cheese enchilada and the red snapper entree.

I went here for brunch. Ordered a glass of rose, which was on the menu, and they were out. How can you be out of rose if you are serving brunch?  They had bottles though. They could have opened one for a glass,  but did not. And no white wine either. I had the chorizo burrito. Portion size was pretty big, but the chorizo was light. I couldn't even taste it, but it was good despite that. Guacamole was good too. They have the options for flavors. Margarita was okay. Overall just an ok place.
If you want to be disrespected, come here!!! Tall guy about 6'2" dark comb to back hair is rude rude and condescending!! Skinny blonde was just as bad!! We left!!!

This place honestly far exceeded my expectations! Though its a bit pricey (like most West Loop restaurants), every single aspect of my meal was phenomenal - I understand why they earned a Michelin Bib Gourmand this past year.  The guapo cocktail was well balanced and strong, would recommend for all mezcal lovers. The cochinita pibil tacos were rich with flavor and were the perfect level of spiciness. My favorite was probably the ceviche trio - each one was so tasty and yet incredibly unique!  I ordered too much because I was super hungry, but I would recommend getting around 1 dish per person. The ambience was lovely (lots of indie rock music!!) and service was crazy fast. I'd love to return!
Great food, tequila flights.  Can't go wrong.

OMG! Loved going back to LaJosie!!!  ❤️👍🏽. Food was delicious as always!!  And the service was super great!!  We had a really great time.  I lived seeing the kitchen so busy with all kinds of take-out/delivery orders. Can't wait to go back!!
Great customer service!
We picked La Josie for our Valentines treat and it met and exceeded our expectations. So beautifully crafted and delicious!! All at a relatively low price. We will definitely be back.

My wife and I, stopped in around 3:30 and were welcomed with warm greetings and seated immediately.  A mask is a must have when entering, being seated, also during  anytime your waiter/waitress is at your table (so be prepared)  Highly recommend the shrimp/fish cerviche trio.  The only disappointment is their black beans and their version of Mexican rice. The black beans were cooked well for texture although bland just like their watery bland rice. Although, it was presented beautifully in tiny little gray earth ware bowls. I also had the steak tacos that were delicious and tender also very flavorful with homemade tortillas.  My wife and I would like to return for happy hour which begins at 4p and we would like to visit in the summer.
Great place for cocktails!!
Did not like the prices.
I usually go here for the drinks! They are top notch
Drinks and food were great! Definitely will come again.
Delicious food.  Smaller portions. Try every taco possible.  Never had one that wasn't delicious.
Good place to go!

La Josie is hands down one of my favorite restaurants in the city. Their ability to keep consistency in flavors, presentation, quality of service, and still somehow to exceed expectations each time you're there is magical.  We’ve done take out, rooftop, indoor, window.  From every angle this restaurant is an incredible experience.  The Pollo rostizado (Adobo) and enchiladas verde (Pollo) with a tropical fruit cocktail are my demise.  My husband is carnitas all day.  If you have help, do the parrillada, because it's an experience to enjoy.  ps. Don't forget the queso fundido and Guacu
Not bad, but not amazed. Will come back for dinner menu and alcohol if got a chance though. Environment is good.
Great food and wonderful service!
The service was excellent, the atmosphere was great, staff was very diligent about their masks, 10/10. Food was beyond delicious and they had the best tequila cocktail I've ever had!!
Great food. Really expensive though

Loose hair in the brussel sprouts, service on the patio was not knowledgeable about the menu and had an irritated attitude throughout our entire meal. Only 1 heater for 6+ tables on the patio. Will not be returning.
The food was absolutely amazing and the staff were wonderful!! Can't wait to go back!

One of the best restaurants I have been to in Chicago. My sister and I had reservations but were about 10 minutes late, they still took us! Our server Eric and the hosts were great. The server made suggestions on the appetizer and the hosts checked on us to make sure we had water. We ordered the asada tacos and pollo (roasted chicken), and the food was delicious and juicy. Definitely get the pollo!

ABSOLUTELY AMAZING. Where do I even begin. Hands down best restaurant we have eaten at in a long time or ever. Best Mexican food ever. Very very kind staff that love their jobs and love where they work. The quality of the food was top notch and I could just go on and on. You need to get the chorizo fondido, shrimp tacos, the red salsa, and the steak enchiladas. Traveled from the Detroit area. WILL BE BACK!! 😍
Best Mexican food I have had in a long time. Chicke n enchiladas suites were delicious. Chicken was smoked. Tomatillo sauce was perfect.

Was rushed the entire time. Foods great, but disappointed with the service. I never write a review, just thought people should know. Came for the bottomless brunch. Only got 30 minutes because the server was leaving.
I went there for brunch. Great rooftop. Bottom Mimosa were great and kept coming.
Not a lot of flavor and expensive.
Excellent food. Friendly service.

Went here for my anniversary dinner with my boyfriend. It was okay.  Staff was attentive, friendly, and courteous.  Cocktails were just okay. Between the both of us we tried 4 different ones and none were a favorite, but they were decent.  Tacos, eh. They need to double up on the tortillas because they were hard to hold and fell apart, but nicely packed. You HAVE to get three of the same, there’s no way to mix and match which is a little annoying since they are “upscale” and more expensive. We would have loved to try more.  THE TRES LECHES! The tres leches was AMAZING and saved the day. It was our favorite and would def go back just for that.  All in all it was an okay experience :)
Awesome Mexican food! Their service was top notch. Also went during Mezcal Week and had a fun experience trying rare, aged mezcals. Highly recommend!
(Translated by Google) magnificent place  (Original) magnifico lugar

Great service during a time where eating out is scary! The staff keep  their distance, had a mask on covering their mouth and nose. The food is always great! I had the lobster tacos and they were delicious!

Nothing special. Food was just okay and overpriced for what you get IMO. Drinks were good but also very expensive. Just your typical trendy brunch spot in West Loop, charging a premium for being across the street from Au Cheval and thus a lot of peoples' second choice.
Delicious salsas and tasty vegan options along with upscale Mexican fare.

Trendy, upscale but casual feeling. Staff is super friendly, they dont rush you out. Very welcoming.  And the drinks are great! We had chips and 3 types of salsa, which were all very good, from mild to spicy to hot! Would go back again.

Food was good but customer service and waiter was just blah. Made a reservation for a Bday and wanted rooftop but couldnt help us out or even try to seat us in two table close for the party and some were very upset.. will see next time 🤦🏽‍♂️
Very good atmosphere and food. I’ve crossed the place without any intention to get in, but I couldn’t resist the good vibes.

The elote and chicken enchiladas were fire and desire. The tropical fruta was ok. Loved the presentation but will try a different drink next time. The flavor did remind me of Cancun with its hints of spice. My friend got the veggie tacos and said they were amazing! Can't wait to go back and try their tacos myself. Came back and had their steak tacos! Bomb! Might have to move this place to my no. 1 taco spot.

Very friend staff. Tons of outdoor and window seating which is great for COVID. We had enchiladas, with and without steak, asada steak tacos, Baja maji tacos, queso, churros, and tres leches banana cake. The drinks are very good. Def will come back to try some other menu items. Good location too. Right in the middle of the West Loop restaurant district.

OMG incredible. Just incredible. Seriously. 100% recommend. If you're debating going, just go! You won't regret. We started with the trio guacamole, and it was even better than expected, the flavors were perfect and I was pleasantly surprised by the fruit guac! Fruit in my guac is not really a thing I'd think I'd like but La Josie proved me totally wrong. The pineapple guac was actually my favorite... Drooling thinking about it. Their house made chips were fantastic. I got the lobster tacos... Oh my gosh...SO good you guys!!! And the tacos were not stingy on the lobster in the slightest. I felt like it was a VERY good amount of big lobster pieces and the price for the tacos is very fair. I would order them again for sure! My husband got the Baja fish tacos and those were also super good. Also, the service was very good! Prompt, paid attention to detail, very friendly, and everyone had their masks above their nose and they were thankfully not wearing gloves (gloves gross me out beyond belief... How long have you had those on? Are they fresh? Unless you're clearing the table, you should not be wearing gloves!) Thanks La Josie!

Great food, drinks and ambiance. Love the outdoor seating.
Great food and Drinks! Lobster tacos and chicken was amazing.

great food. good prices and great service.

We was told that there are bars behind that we can sit and wait for our table and so we did. 10 minutes at the bar later I got myself a drink and there are only two seats. Your flavors are exceptional! Everything from the drinks, to the salsa, and the tacos.  The choice of seasoning is on a another level. My wife ordered the al pastor and I ordered the lobster tacos. Came here to celebrate a graduation. Wanted a vibe that was classy but fun and relaxing. Josie fit the bill. The ambiance was perfect. Staff was friendly . But let's get to the food part as all is forgiven when it tastes good. I for one like to order ceviche if it's on the menu. It's my constant search for the best ceviche that wasn't made by me at home. I think for now Josie has it. They have a mahi mahi ceviche, it is made similar to Peruvian style but with mahi mahi. The leche de tigre has some passion fruit touch to it which compliments the lime and makes the flavors all come together in a sweet harmony of sounds playing at your taste buds stage. The toughest part with restaurant ceviche is preparing the fish quickly and they nailed it. Quite often there isn't enough time for the lime to "cook" its way into the fish and the fish is left tasting bland. La Josie managing to avoid this, I'm curious how! It came with a side of soda crackers which complimented the dish well. The rest of my group enjoyed the same dish of enchiladas with mole and chicken. When I looked up I saw all 5 dishes cleaned off so it's safe to assume it was equally as delicious. We had some guacamole as appetizer and it was good as one can expect, you can't go messing that up. They did have a pinnacle guacamole which I had never had before and will try to duplicate at home for sure. I was left pleasantly surprised as I was scared this would be a other Mexican upscale abomination that can happen in Chicago. Most times you are better off going to a mom and pop spot. But you can taste the passion from this chef, they even brought our Mexican grandmother a sauce she liked original to Mexico. Not only will I come here again, I also didn't indulge in the caste selection of tequilas...tear drops, but I'm truly excited to taste more food. In conclusion, La Josie better be paying that chef well and kudos to the kind owner who has stayed true to the roots and focused on the flavor more than anything.

WOW, the food here is incredible. We had traditional guac, shrimp quesadillas, and chicken enchiladas with salsa Verde. Amazing. The guac was fresh and well balanced. The enchiladas were very very good, all fresh, big portion, and just right level of spicy. This place was packed on a Friday night, with an hour wait at 9:30 pm. We got lucky and got a seat at the bar, but you'll certainly want a reservation. Awesome west loop Mexican option!

We chose the  asada and pollo rostizado tacos off of the "Tres Tacos" selection on the menu and shared them.   While the asada tacos were good,  the pollo rostizado tacos were EVERYTHING.   I've been unsuccessfully trying to recreate it at home with no success.   I wanted to have a cocktail but it was so hot. And that's why I didn't give this restaurant 5 stars.   The weather outside was so warm and they kept serving lukewarm water with no ice.   Other than that,  I'd most definitely  recommend it.
